    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/61395246/2bac3213-cf6c-4f1b-a71c-0c1b9f514cd2\r\n\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI am looking at submitting a PR to make the behavior of `vim.api.nvim_buf_set_text` identical to the normal behavior expected when adding text in `set va=all`.\r\nI see a lot of plugins constantly \"padding\"  their characters when inserting them in a column position that is not \"allocated\" to the line yet.\r\nAnd i think its a shame since the behavior of the editor when setting text at that `col` is as expected, to add the text where its supposed to ,silently  padding it.\r\n\r\nBefore i start i would like some feedback, and more importantly if this PR would be welcomed by the maintainers, and if not why ?",
