            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "How does the negative columns PR solve the issue though?\r\nIf i want to instert text in a line with 0 characters i will still have to pad it manually in lua and the set the text.\r\nThis issue recoments to solve this manual and error prone task by hiding it in the neovim api + making it potentially faster\r\n\r\n>  I think not validating the range would be a confusing, error-prone behavior\r\n\r\nI do agree in a sense with this ( even if this is mostly for user errors ) that it would be preferable for something like `strict_indexing` to be added, just like in\r\n```\r\nnvim_buf_get_lines({buffer}, {start}, {end}, {strict_indexing})\r\n...\r\n      â€¢ {strict_indexing}  Whether out-of-bounds should be an error.\r\n...\r\n```",
